article.headline: Ball St. 71, N. Illinois 60
article.story: MUNCIE, Ind. (AP) -- Three players scored 16 points each as Ball State snapped a six-game losing streak by beating Northern Illinois 71-60 on Tuesday night. Skip Mills, Micah Rollin and Anthony Newell each scored 16 for Ball State (5-12, 1-3 Mid-American Conference). Peyton Stovall had five assists for the Cardinals, who outscored the Huskies 26-9 off the bench, including Newell's 16 points. Mike McKinney led Northern Illinois (4-12, 1-3) with 20 points and Ryan Paradise scored 16 for the Huskies, who have lost 12 of their last 13 games. The Huskies led by 22-16 with 10:29 left in the first half, but Newell's jumper set off a 12-5 run over 5:45 that gave Ball State a 28-27 edge. The Cardinals never trailed again.
